===Etymology===
1775, from {{compound|hand|cuff|t2=end of shirtsleeve}}.<ref name="oetlyd">{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}</ref>

Possibly influenced by {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|handcops|lang=ang}}, from {{term|hand|lang=ang}} + {{term|cops||fetter, chains|lang=ang}}, but due to lack of continuity (centuries between Old English and modern term), generally analyzed as a re-invention.<ref name="oetlyd" />

===Noun===
{{head|en|noun}}

# {{context|plurale tantum|lang=en}} A [[fastening]] consisting of two [[metal]] [[ring]]s, designed to go around a person's [[wrist]]s, and connected by a [[chain]] or [[hinge]].
